<%@ Control Language="C#" AutoEventWireup="true" CodeBehind="HowToPackage.ascx.cs" Inherits="Secureship.Controls.Country.HowToPackage" %>


<section id="how-to-package" class="how-to-package">
    <div>
        <i class="fas fa-box-open"></i>
        <h2>How To Package</h2>
    </div>
    <br />
    <p>
        When sending packages to <%=CountryName %>, a very important factor to consider is the packaging. Improper packaging can lead to 
                damaged goods, delays in delivery time, and risk your shipment being rejected by Customs authorities.
    </p>
    <p>
        Your packaging needs to meet <a target="_blank" href="/learningcenter/shipping-102-your-packaging-responsibilities"
            title="How to safely package your items to <%=CountryName %>">ISTA 3A Standards</a>
        (International Safe Transit Association 3A Standard) to be 
                eligible for an insurance claim should the shipment become damaged.
    </p>
    <p>
        If you&#8217;re looking for the best way to package your product, it might be worth trying the 
        <a target="_blank"  title="UPS packaging advisor will provide additional guidance on how to prepare your packages for shipment to <%=CountryName %>"
            href="https://www.ups.com/packaging/?loc=en_US">UPS Packaging Advisor</a>. There you will find recommendations based on the size, weight, and contents of your package.
    </p>


    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-4 col-sm-7 col-xs-5">
            <img class="lazyLoad"
                src="//d1n9d69im4r2us.cloudfront.net/website/images/1x1.gif"
                data-src="/webship/images/notifications/minimum_packaging_requirement.png"
                alt="Minimum packaging standard for shipments to <%=CountryName %>"
                title="Minimum packaging standard for your parcel to <%=CountryName %>" />
            <noscript>
                <img
                    src="/webship/images/notifications/minimum_packaging_requirement.png"
                    alt="Minimum packaging standard for shipments to <%=CountryName %>"
                    title="Minimum packaging standard for your parcel to <%=CountryName %>" />
            </noscript>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-8 col-sm-12 col-xs-12">
            <p>
                You can <b class="emphasis">reduce the risk of damage</b> by:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>Packing the container with at least 2" of padding between the product and the wall of the container</li>
                <li>Using at least 2" of padding between each product</li>
                <li>Using adequate cushioning material</li>
                <li>Using a double corrugated cardboard box </li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
    <p>
        <br />
        For more information on proper packaging, check out our guide <a
            title="Shipping 102: Your packaging responsibilities and how to prepare your goods for transportation"
            href="/learningcenter/shipping-102-your-packaging-responsibilities">Shipping 102: Your Packaging Responsibilities</a>.
    </p>
</section>
